==English==

===Etymology===
From Latin ''[[assertum]]'', past participle of ''[[asserere]]'' "claim", from ''[[ad-]]'' + ''[[serere]]'' "join"

===Pronunciation===
*{{IPA|[[RP]] /əˈsɜːt/}}

===Verb===
{{en-infl-reg-consonant|assert||}}

# To [[affirm]]; to [[declare]] with [[assurance]] or plainly and strongly; to state positively; to [[ave]]r; to [[asseverate]].
# To [[maintain]]; to [[defend]].
# To maintain or defend, as a [[cause]] or a [[claim]], by words or measures; to [[vindicate]] a claim or title to; as, to assert our rights and liberties.

